==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Stillness
<hw>Still"ness</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The
quality or state of being still; quietness; silence; calmness;
inactivity.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Painting, then, was the art demanded by the modern intellect upon
its emergence from the <qex>stillness</qex> of the Middle Ages.</q>
<rj><qau>J. A. Symonds.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Habitual silence or quiet; taciturnity.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The gravity and <qex>stillness</qex> of your youth⟦br⟧
The world hath noted.</q> <rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Stillroom</ent>⟦br⟧
